# Gang Wars — Locked UI Layout Standards

These layouts are **unchangeable standards**. Match `docs/ui-standards/*.png` exactly. Do not refactor, restyle, or "improve" them.

## Portrait only

- Game is **portrait-only** — layout never reflows for landscape
- `manifest.json`: `"orientation": "portrait-primary"`
- `#portrait-root` uses a CSS rotate on touch landscape so the portrait layout stays fixed while the device moves
- JS attempts `screen.orientation.lock('portrait')` when supported (installed PWA)
- Desktop browsers (fine pointer) are unaffected — `#crt` stays `max-width:540px` centered

## 1. Event popups (`.ev-popup`)

Reference: `docs/ui-standards/popup.png`

- **50/50 split**: CSS grid `1fr 1fr` — `.ev-left` column 1, `.ev-right` column 2
- **Full-bleed art**: zero padding on `.ev-left`; `background-size:cover; background-position:top left` — no letterboxing or gaps
- All popup PNGs processed through `scripts/event_art.py` `export_panel()` — trim outer black gutter, enhance, scale to 662px height
- All tier event PNGs (`rare_*`, `super_*`, `godlike_*`) normalized to 662px height via `scripts/normalize-event-art.py --all`
- Gold vertical divider between panels (`border-left: 1px solid var(--amber)`)
- All narrative/event popups use `showEvent` / `showEventAsk` / feds `draw()` — never plain `.card` for events
- Standard event art: 10 PNGs in `events/` from `assets/event-grid-source.png` via `scripts/split-event-grid.py` — do not hand-edit; re-slice from source if needed
- Form modals (trade qty, bank) stay on `.card` — they are exempt

## 2. Travel screen (`.travel-play`)

Reference: `docs/ui-standards/travel.png`

- **Header**: full side-view car (`assets/travel-car.png`) via `scripts/extract-travel-car.py` from `docs/ui-standards/travel.png` — `object-fit:contain`, `height:100%`, `max-width:44%`, vertically centered; no border box; never crop the car
- **District list**: six equal-height rows, **zero gap** — stacked with horizontal dividers only, no rounded card gaps or dead space
- **Footer**: compact "GO BACK" bar
- Outer frame: `3px double var(--amber)` on `.travel-screen`
- Single-screen, no scroll

## 3. End screens (`.eos`)

Reference: `docs/ui-standards/end-screen.png`

- **Portrait stack** (top → bottom): FINAL SCORE + Tommy guns + amount → high-score table → rank card → PLAY AGAIN / MAIN MENU
- **Score header**: `assets/eos-tommy-left.png` flanking amount (mirrored right); rule line below
- **Rank card**: full `cards/{rank}.png` in `.eos-card` gold frame — cards normalized via `scripts/prepare-eos-assets.py` (400px wide + 1px black pad)
- **Outside top 10**: player row in `.eos-you-box` with gold border
- Every game-over path must use `renderGameOver()` / `.eos` — no alternate end layouts
- Single-screen, no scroll

## When editing

If a task would change popup, travel, or end-screen structure, spacing, image fit, or borders — **stop and ask the user first**.
